WhileÂ tinkering with Django for some personal project of mine I'd needed to visualize a graph. That reason to me into an exploration of graph libraries and I came across two libraries that could do the job for me: <a href="http://sigmajs.org/">Sigma.js</a> and <a href="http://getspringy.com/">Springy.js</a> After an evening of fiddling around I wanted to share my result:
<a href="http://www.jplattel.nl/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Screen-Shot-2014-10-24-at-5.07.07-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3119" src="http://www.jplattel.nl/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Screen-Shot-2014-10-24-at-5.07.07-PM.png" alt="Screen Shot 2014-10-24 at 5.07.07 PM" width="666" height="464" /></a>
Sadly, the documentation for <a href="http://sigmajs.org/">Sigma.js</a> is somewhat lacking. It's up to you to find out trough examples how the code works. If I had the time I would surely provide some additional docs trough Github. For now here, are some of my problems (and solutions):
<!--more-->
<h4>Force Directed</h4>
Springy.js does it out of the box. But it took me a while to figure out how to do it with Sigma.js:
<pre>&lt;script src="path_to/plugins/sigma.layout.forceAtlas2.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
s = new sigma({}) // create a graph here and create nodes and edges
s.refresh(); 
s.startForceAtlas2(); // Start with force directing nodes
s.stopForceAtlas2();  // Stop force directing (with a button or timeout)
&lt;/script&gt;</pre>
<h4>(Search)Â Filters</h4>
A filter works like a lens, it can be added or removed. If you, for example are running a search across a graph, you would apply a lens with a certain string. That string can be matched on each node label (or description or whatever) and it would return true for each node that matches it. Finally that filter applies styling for each node depending on the result:
<pre>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
var filter = new sigma.plugins.filter(s);
$('#search').click(function(e){
  filter.undo('search').apply() // Undo filter
  e.preventDefault(); // prevent submit
  filter.nodesBy(function(n) { // loop trough all nodes
    return ~n.label.toLowerCase().indexOf($('#search').val().toLowerCase()) // match the label to search string case insensitive
  },'search').apply(); // Apply the filter
  s.refresh(); // Refresh the graph
});
&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
